The Downfall of Bakhtíyár Khiljí : Rout of his Force by Tibet and Kámarúpa&quot;
A man who is sickened with grief, surrounded by depression, a man who is languishing in his own pathetic misery. A man who is too ashamed to come out of his room! Surely, one should feel sorry for any such creature and pity his situation, right? But that doesn’t always happen. For empathy is an emotion that is not absolute.
